From 0000000000000000000000000000000000000037 Mon Sep 17 00:00:00 2001
From: Henry AI <henry.ai@example.com>
Date: Thu, 9 Jul 2026 21:35:00 +0800
Subject: [PATCH] pcie-rockchip-dma: clear observed client error status after DMA IRQ

The immediate golden129 PCIe tests show that both a 4-byte ACK DMA and a
single 1MiB DATA_SND DMA can complete with UDMA CH0_DONE on mainline.
However DATA_SND also raises a repeated client interrupt status 0x410
(LOCAL | NFATAL_ERR). The vendor-derived handler only clears LOCAL in the
final client-status write, so NFATAL_ERR can remain pending and storm the
subsystem IRQ even though the UDMA done path has completed.

For the RK3399Pro NPU DMA-enabled path, clear all client status bits that
were observed at IRQ entry after handling the local/core and UDMA status.
Keep the legacy LOCAL-only clear when the DMA bridge is not enabled. Also
print decoded bit names for last_subsys_core and last_client_irq_status so
future board logs directly show NFATAL_ERR/MMVC without manual decoding.

Defaults remain safe: dma_disabled=1 and real DMA is still debugfs opt-in.

Signed-off-by: Henry AI <henry.ai@example.com>
---
diff --git a/drivers/pci/controller/pcie-rockchip-dma.c b/drivers/pci/controller/pcie-rockchip-dma.c
index d31471c..6e22999 100644
--- a/drivers/pci/controller/pcie-rockchip-dma.c
+++ b/drivers/pci/controller/pcie-rockchip-dma.c
@@ -1551,6 +1551,12 @@ static int rk_pcie_debugfs_trx_show(struct seq_file *s, void *v)
 		   dma_obj->dma_irq_sample_period_ms,
 		   dma_obj->dma_irq_sample_count,
 		   dma_obj->dma_irq_sample_tick);
+	rk_pcie_dma_seq_bits(s, "last_subsys_core_bits = ",
+			      dma_obj->last_subsys_core_status, rk_pcie_core_bits,
+			      ARRAY_SIZE(rk_pcie_core_bits));
+	rk_pcie_dma_seq_bits(s, "last_client_irq_status_bits = ",
+			      dma_obj->last_client_irq_status, rk_pcie_client_bits,
+			      ARRAY_SIZE(rk_pcie_client_bits));
 	rk_pcie_dma_seq_bits(s, "client_status_bits = ",
 			      dma_obj->last_client_status, rk_pcie_client_bits,
 			      ARRAY_SIZE(rk_pcie_client_bits));
diff --git a/drivers/pci/controller/pcie-rockchip-host.c b/drivers/pci/controller/pcie-rockchip-host.c
index d908cab..606eb8e 100644
--- a/drivers/pci/controller/pcie-rockchip-host.c
+++ b/drivers/pci/controller/pcie-rockchip-host.c
@@ -585,8 +585,19 @@ static irqreturn_t rockchip_pcie_subsys_irq_handler(int irq, void *arg)
 		rockchip_pcie_write(rockchip, reg, PCIE_CLIENT_INT_STATUS);
 	}
 
-	rockchip_pcie_write(rockchip, reg & PCIE_CLIENT_INT_LOCAL,
-			    PCIE_CLIENT_INT_STATUS);
+	/*
+	 * Vendor 4.4 clears only LOCAL here.  With the RK3399Pro NPU DMA
+	 * endpoint on mainline, a completed DATA_SND can report 0x410
+	 * (LOCAL | NFATAL_ERR).  Clearing only LOCAL leaves NFATAL_ERR pending
+	 * and causes a client IRQ storm while UDMA CH0_DONE has already arrived.
+	 * In DMA mode clear every status bit observed at IRQ entry; keep the
+	 * legacy LOCAL-only behavior for non-DMA host use.
+	 */
+	if (rockchip->dma_trx_enabled)
+		rockchip_pcie_write(rockchip, reg, PCIE_CLIENT_INT_STATUS);
+	else
+		rockchip_pcie_write(rockchip, reg & PCIE_CLIENT_INT_LOCAL,
+				    PCIE_CLIENT_INT_STATUS);
 
 	return IRQ_HANDLED;
 }
